library("ggplot2")
library("palmerpenguins")
ggplot(data=penguins)+
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y= body_mass_g,color=species))+
               labs(title="Palmer Penguins-Body Mass Vs Bill Length", 
                    subtitle ="Three Penguin Species",
                    caption = "Data collected by Dr.Kristen Gorman")+
  annotate("text",x=220,y=3000,label="The Gentoos are
           Largest Penguins",color="Blue",fontface="bold",size=4.5,angle=25)
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

p <- ggplot(data=penguins)+
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y= body_mass_g,color=species))+
  labs(title="Palmer Penguins-Body Mass Vs Bill Length", 
       subtitle ="Three Penguin Species",
       caption = "Data collected by Dr.Kristen Gorman")+
  annotate("text",x=220,y=3000,label="The Gentoos are
           Largest Penguins",color="Blue",fontface="bold",size=4.5,angle=25)
g <- ggplot(data=penguins)+
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y= body_mass_g,color=species))+
  labs(title="Palmer Penguins-Body Mass Vs Bill Length", 
       subtitle ="Three Penguin Species",
       caption = "Data collected by Dr.Kristen Gorman")
g+annotate("text", x=220,y=3000,label=" Gentoos largest")
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

ggsave("Three Penguins Species.png")
